    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a large heat-proof bowl covered with <strong>cling film</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 5-8 min or until slightly tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>baby button mushrooms </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are starting to crisp, add your <strong>smoked streaky</strong> <strong>bacon </strong>to the other side of the tray[s] with your <strong>halved mushrooms </strong>and <strong>halved tomato</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> the tomato and mushroom and season with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 9-10 min or until the bacon is lightly golden</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>finely</p><p>Combine your <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> and <strong>kimchi ketchup</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>kimchi ketchup</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender and the bacon is lightly golden, remove the tray[s] from the oven, move your bacon on top of your potatoes and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>on to the tray[s]</p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for a perfectly centred yolk!</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-5 min or until the egg is done to your liking and the bacon is crisp and golden</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-bacon-egg-cheesy-potatoes-with-kimchi-ketchup/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bacon</strong>, <strong>egg</strong>,<strong> mushrooms</strong>, <strong>roasted tomato </strong>and the<strong> golden potatoes</strong></p><p>Top the potatoes with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>kimchi ketchup</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
